HEADWORD: Annuloida
<hw>An`nu*loid"a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>annulus</ets> ring + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of the Articulata, including the
annelids and allied groups; sometimes made to include also the helminths
and echinoderms.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Annuloidea</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annulosa</ent>⟦br⟧
